{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Redefine the term \u2018majority\u2019 in regards to referendums as a minimum of 65%.",
        "additional_details": "In other countries, such as the US, a major change to the constitution requires two-thirds majority in both the Senate and House of Representatives. The fact that in the UK a result of just over 50% can constitute a major change can and has led to major social divisions within the country whilst also meaning that the will of a significant portion of the population goes unheeded. This makes the country vulnerable to disinformation.\r\n\r\nhttps://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-eu-referendum-36306681",
        "background": "52% is NOT  majority; this means that the will of a significant portion of the population goes unheeded. The government needs to redefine the term 'majority' in a referendum to 65% minimum.",
